The paper deals with comparing shapes, which is a common problem in computer graphics (cs.CG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of linear operators and norms suggests a connection to geometric representation (cs.GR) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The coreset construction and approximation algorithms are related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
